				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>+</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px">
f++: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
+(params)
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center">
n++: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
\@+(params)
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					<mono>+</mono> is the arithmetic operator for <u>addition</u>, it takes a non-zero number of input parameters, if all parameters are numbers it returns their sum, otherwise it returns their string concatenation.
				</p>

				<p>
					<b>Note:</b> It is typically faster to use <a href="@pathtopage(docs/exprtk)">exprtk</a> for arithmetic operators, plus the syntax is nicer.
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>+</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
:=(int, a=10, b=13, c=15)
:=(string, str="hello")
console(+(a, b))
console(+(a, b, c))
console(+(str, ", ", "world!"))</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>+</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
\@:=(int, a=10, b=13, c=15)
\@:=(string, str="hello")
\@console(\@+(a, b))
\@console(\@+(a, b, c))
\@console(\@+(str, ", ", "world!"))</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</section>
